RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 103. Claiming Purse 44000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 31 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000, if for $35,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden And Claiming Races For $32,000 Or Less Not Co nsidered In Allowances). (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOR A LAUGH (IRE) stalked along the rail, tipped out into the lane, drew alongside GIOVINAZZO with a furlong remaining and proved best late. GIOVINAZZO showed early speed from inside, set all the pace to the stretch, challenged at the eighth pole, resisted into deep stretch and yielded late. FLAVIUS tracked two to the far turn, tipped three wide at the quarter pole, chased within striking range with a furlong remaining, faltered in the late stages but managed to edge INDIAN PEAK for third. INDIAN PEAK settled inside at the back, shifted to the two path on the far turn but lacked room at the quarter pole and altered back to the fence, put in a rail bid with a furlong remaining but flattened out. ORIGINAL broke well, raced up close in the two path, ridden along on the far turn, started to lose ground past the quarter pole and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAZEN IN THE SUN broke a step slow, chased from inside then angled out on the backstretch, bid four deep on the turn, dueled in upper stretch, put away the runner-up past the eight pole and drew away. R GIRL'S WERTH IT raced up close on the inside then ceded to outer rivals, bid along the rail at the five-sixteenths pole, took over approaching the quarter pole, dueled with GRAZEN IN THE SUN in upper stretch and was no match for that rival in the furlong grounds. MISS COMMANDER forced to steady when GRAZEN IN THE SUN angled out early, chased three wide into the turn, angled down to the inside around the bend, steered out in upper stretch and gained the show. WINK WISH AND PARK dueled inside a rival up the backstretch, vied two wide around the bend and lost command outside the quarter pole, then weakened down the stretch. HOUSE OF TARGARYEN raced in range well off the rail, rounded the bend five wide and weakened. THREE POINT OH dueled for the lead from outside to the turn, vied three deep on the bend, chased the leaders past the quarter pole and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 90. Maiden Special Weight Purse 65000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred). (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THIRTY CARATS forwardly placed three deep then two wide into the backstretch, moved up to press at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled into the stretch, took over from PRINCESS MIDNIGHT, cleared midstretch and held well. NO NO NO NEVER (IRE) stalked from inside, came off the rail a bit a the top of the lane then angled out further and finished determinedly for second. PRINCESS MIDNIGHT broke out and bothered HERON BAY, took control early outside a rival then cleared and moved to the rail around the clubhouse turn, took pressure leaving the backstretch, dueled on the far turn, lost command in upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. BOLT'S BROAD settled along the fence moved a bit off the rail on the far turn then came back inside, steered out in the lane and missed the show. MACHIAVELLIQUE brushed leaving the gate, sat off the pace in the two path, gained three then two wide on the far turn but faltered in the final furlong. NO WAY IT'S TODAY (GB) rated between foes then outside a rival, coaxed along leaving the backstretch but got put in a bit tight entering the far turn, trailed two wide into the lane and could not rally. HERON BAY got brushed and crowded at the start, angled to the inside trailing the field, angled out and won on the move three deep on the backstretch, chased three to four wide into the lane and flattened out.

ENTRY.NAME: Bolt's Broad
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, moved out str, missed 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Midnight
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, led 2wide-inside, dueled inside, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 67000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Claiming Price $50,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Null).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KRISTI'S TIGER raced in range up the backstretch, traveled along the rail into the turn, came under a ride around the bend while tipping out to the three path, closed in on the leaders entering the final sixteenth and drove past. BLESSED TOUCH stalked three wide into the turn, bid three deep at the quarter pole, took over approaching the final furlong, held a short lead into deep stretch but could not offer any resistance to the winner late. VITALERA (CHI) set the pace up the backstretch outside LLORONA, lost command to that rival near the five-sixteenths pole, regained the lead at the quarter pole, relinquished the lead to BLESSED TOUCH outside the furlong marker and stayed on for a clear third. LLORONA raced up close then pressed from inside early, took over midway around the turn, lost command at the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. PROFESSORS' PRIDE hopped at the start spotting the field several lengths, drew closer up the backstretch, raced two wide into the turn then moved over to the rail, drifted into the lane and had little left for the stretch run. R SWIRVIN GIRVIN tracked widest early, went three then two wide on the turn, got floated out by PROFESSORS' PRIDE leaving the bend and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 96. Starter Allowance Purse 39000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUGELACH vied between rivals up the backstretch and around the turn, inched ahead in upper stretch and edged away in the final sixteenth. FAST GISELLE vied for command three deep to the top of the stretch, dueled outside RUGELACH to midstretch, yielded to that rival and stayed on to secure second. RVALENTINA moved inside stalking the top trio, chased along the rail then lacked room while shifting to the two path at the quarter pole, lacked room behind the leader again in upper stretch, moved to the inside to put in a mild bid but could not sustain the momentum late. STRANGE ADDICTION broke a step slow, trailed early on the inside then inside rivals into the turn, advanced along the fence through the bend, angled out in upper stretch but finished evenly late. READY JET GO sat off the pace off the rail then three deep into the turn, went between foes around the bend then two wide into the stretch and could not rally. INNER BEAUTY (IRE) chased the leading trio outside a rival three wide into the turn, moved into the two path then came three wide into the stretch and lacked a bid. GYPSY LYNN held a narrow lead early inside a pair of rivals up the backstretch, fought through the turn continuing to save ground, lost command leaving the bend and weakened down the lane. ICE QUEEN chased out of range four wide into the turn, entered the lane three wide and failed to menace. LITTLE LILIANA chased off the pace then between rivals into the turn, got crowded at the three eighths pole then drifted out on the turn and was not persevered with.

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, inside, advanced inside, altered out upper, evenly

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, traffic 1/4 & upper, bid inside, faltered

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 31 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEARTFULLOFSTARS broke a step slow, trailed then was coaxed along near the back early, went three wide into the turn, moved to the two path then angled five wide late on the bend, closed well from the middle portion of the track, took over midstretch and edged away. NAUVOO stalked the top pair from outside, rounded the bend three then four wide, challenged between rivals midstretch but was outclosed by the winner. AFTERNOON HEAT laid off the pace well off the inside, navigated the turn five then six wide, moved inward in the stretch and was along for the show honors. HANDR'SDREAM broke well and chased for a bit before pressing from outside, dueled around the turn and inched ahead at the quarter pole, put away inner rival in upper stretch, relinquished the lead midstretch and flattened to fourth. HIGH PRESS broke slow and came in at the start, chased out of range on the inside and failed to respond when asked. WHOA BUDDY unhurried in the early going, took the turn four then three wide and failed to menace. TOM BOMBADIL sped clear then set the pace inside HANDR'SDREAM up the backstretch, dueled with that rival and lost command at the quarter pole, failed to kick on with the leader in upper stretch and weakened. MR. MASON tracked four wide into the turn, spun five wide into the lane, weakened and eased in the stretch and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Lady of Shamrock S. SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 109. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLD FILLIES. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, December 21, 2023, closed with 18 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry, closed with 1 (Luminiferous). $750 to enter and an additional $750 t o start with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Weight 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at One Mile or over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of A Race other than Ma iden, Claiming or Starter at One Mile or Over allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUBY NELL took control early and established a comfortable advantage on the inside, held a diminished lead into the far turn, kicked away again without being urged, asked right handed entering the lane and responded by opening up in upper stretch, asked once left handed past the eighth pole and was ridden out in the final sixteenth. JUSTIQUE raced well off the pace on the inside early, gained along the rail on the far turn, tipped three wide into the stretch, finished willingly in the stretch to gain the place but could not threaten the winner. IRISH PATSY trailed on the inside into the first turn then went outside a rival, rounded the far turn two to three wide and offered a mild response to gain the show. ANACARO broke well then took a stalking position in the two path, moved to the rail on the far turn, came out a bit in upper stretch and weakened. CLIQUISH stalked along the rail, eased out to the four path on the far turn and asked right handed but weakened down the lane. PRINCESS BETTINA stalked in the two path early, three deep in the middle stages, came back to the two path on the far while closest in pursuit, then faded in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Ruby Nell
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, asked, widened, much the best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 107. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 69000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $80,000. Claiming Price $80,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOST OF MIDNIGHT chased four then three wide early, continued in the three path on the far turn, reached the front midstretch and maintained a short lead to the wire. ARROWTHEGREAT forwardly placed three then two wide on the clubhouse turn, pressed from outside up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn and took over late on the bend, lost command midstretch and stayed on gamely inside the winner. MCLAREN VALE set the pace in the two path then moved inside, pressured up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn and lost command, fought to the sixteenth pole and faltered late. OVIATT CLASS settled in the two path, driven three wide into the lane, moved out and could not rally. ARHAM pulled while trying to rate on the inside, coaxed along on the far turn, came two wide into the drive and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 65000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BABY WAYLON coaxed to the front and crossed over to the inside, set the pace under pressure to the far turn, dueled around the bend and lost command past the quarter pole, regained the lead while brushing with KISS FOR LULU near the eighth pole and held gamely to the wire. KISS FOR LULU ceded the lead early then went up to press from outside, raced on even terms on the far turn and took over past the quarter pole, drifted in and brushed BABY WAYLON near the eighth pole, battled into deep stretch and finished gamely in defeat. CLEMENTS RIDE broke a step slow then had to steady early, traveled two wide then along the inside off the pace, tipped back to the two path on the far turn, closed well and gained the show. TWILIGHT MOON pulled early on the inside early then drifted out into the first turn, steered back to the rail around the bend, saved ground through the far turn and could not rally in the drive. TAKES THREE broke well then became rank when rated early and two then three wide on the first turn, stalked outside a rival through the second bend, asked right handed entering the lane and finished evenly. JIMMY'S WILD BOY came away slow, chased outside a rival then three wide into the first turn before moving to the inside, saved ground to the stretch, moved out in the lane and lacked a rally. RUN BRYCE RUN chased three deep into the first turn then drifted out before being corrected, raced near the back on the backstretch, two wide into the far turn, angled out to the four path, steered back in during the stretch run and failed to menace. DRIVE FOR SHOW chased between rivals then got floated out on the clubhouse turn, raced in mid-pack on the backstretch, three deep on the far turn and weakened. MOTIVATING FORCE broke a step slow, raced outside rivals then altered out approaching the first turn then got floated out early on the bend, advanced four then three deep on the far turn, then flattened out in the lane.
